"{\"uid\": \"theguardian.com-environment-article-2024-aug-30-olympic-champion-etienne-stott-joins-climate-activists-for-windsor-protest\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"Etienne Stott among Extinction Rebellion protesters to call for citizens' assembly to tackle climate crisis An Olympic gold medal-winning canoeist will be among climate activists protesting in Windsor this weekend to demand theLabourgovernment takes climate action seriously.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 276, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 0, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Etienne_Stott\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Etienne Stott\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Etienne_Stott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Etienne_Stott\"}, {\"begin\": 194, \"end\": 201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Windsor_Castle\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.191055777882387e-16, \"text\": \"Windsor\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Windsor_Castle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Windsor_Castle\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Extinction Rebellion protesters\", \"from\": 20, \"to\": 51}, {\"ngram\": \"citizens' assembly\", \"from\": 64, \"to\": 82}, {\"ngram\": \"climate crisis\", \"from\": 93, \"to\": 107}, {\"ngram\": \"An Olympic gold medal-winning canoeist\", \"from\": 108, \"to\": 146}, {\"ngram\": \"climate activists\", \"from\": 161, \"to\": 178}, {\"ngram\": \"theLabourgovernment\", \"from\": 224, \"to\": 243}, {\"ngram\": \"climate action\", \"from\": 250, \"to\": 264}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Extinction Rebellion, which is organising the three-day event, which began on Friday, said it had been disappointed by the new administration's lack of action on reducing fossil fuel emissions.\", \"from\": 278, \"to\": 471, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Extinction Rebellion\", \"from\": 278, \"to\": 298}, {\"ngram\": \"the three-day event\", \"from\": 320, \"to\": 339}, {\"ngram\": \"Friday\", \"from\": 356, \"to\": 362}, {\"ngram\": \"the new administration's lack\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 426}, {\"ngram\": \"action\", \"from\": 430, \"to\": 436}, {\"ngram\": \"fossil fuel emissions\", \"from\": 449, \"to\": 470}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The event includes a funfair, a large campsite, speakers, art and music.\", \"from\": 473, \"to\": 545, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The event\", \"from\": 473, \"to\": 482}, {\"ngram\": \"a funfair\", \"from\": 492, \"to\": 501}, {\"ngram\": \"a large campsite\", \"from\": 503, \"to\": 519}, {\"ngram\": \"speakers\", \"from\": 521, \"to\": 529}, {\"ngram\": \"art\", \"from\": 531, \"to\": 534}, {\"ngram\": \"music\", \"from\": 539, \"to\": 544}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A few of the actions will be centred around Windsor Castle but, contrary to media reports, the activists say they have no plans to \\\"storm the castle\\\" and that all events will be non-disruptive.\", \"from\": 546, \"to\": 739, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the actions\", \"from\": 555, \"to\": 566}, {\"ngram\": \"Windsor Castle\", \"from\": 590, \"to\": 604}, {\"ngram\": \"media reports\", \"from\": 622, \"to\": 635}, {\"ngram\": \"the activists\", \"from\": 637, \"to\": 650}, {\"ngram\": \"no plans\", \"from\": 665, \"to\": 673}, {\"ngram\": \"the castle\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 694}, {\"ngram\": \"all events\", \"from\": 705, \"to\": 715}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Activists are calling on the government to set up a citizens' assembly to tackle the climate crisis.\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 841, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Activists\", \"from\": 741, \"to\": 750}, {\"ngram\": \"the government\", \"from\": 766, \"to\": 780}, {\"ngram\": \"a citizens' assembly\", \"from\": 791, \"to\": 811}, {\"ngram\": \"the climate crisis\", \"from\": 822, \"to\": 840}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Etienne Stott, XR UK spokesperson and an Olympic gold medal-winning canoeist, said: \\\"The first job of the state is to protect its citizens and keep them safe.\", \"from\": 843, \"to\": 1001, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 843, \"end\": 856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Etienne_Stott\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Etienne Stott\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Etienne_Stott\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Etienne_Stott\"}, {\"begin\": 861, \"end\": 863, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999997752975357, \"rank\": 8.897875615327145e-08, \"text\": \"UK\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"an Olympic gold medal-winning canoeist\", \"from\": 881, \"to\": 919}, {\"ngram\": \"The first job\", \"from\": 928, \"to\": 941}, {\"ngram\": \"the state\", \"from\": 945, \"to\": 954}, {\"ngram\": \"its citizens\", \"from\": 969, \"to\": 981}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Politicians are too close to and too compromised by the vested interests of the oil barons and media billionaires to carry out this primary duty of care.\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1155, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Politicians\", \"from\": 1002, \"to\": 1013}, {\"ngram\": \"the vested interests\", \"from\": 1054, \"to\": 1074}, {\"ngram\": \"the oil barons\", \"from\": 1078, \"to\": 1092}, {\"ngram\": \"media\", \"from\": 1097, \"to\": 1102}, {\"ngram\": \"this primary duty\", \"from\": 1129, \"to\": 1146}, {\"ngram\": \"care\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1154}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A citizens' assembly is a proven mechanism that can be deployed to bypass these corrupting influences and get things done in a way that is fair for all and bridges political divides.\\\"\", \"from\": 1156, \"to\": 1339, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A citizens' assembly\", \"from\": 1156, \"to\": 1176}, {\"ngram\": \"a proven mechanism\", \"from\": 1180, \"to\": 1198}, {\"ngram\": \"these corrupting influences\", \"from\": 1230, \"to\": 1257}, {\"ngram\": \"things\", \"from\": 1266, \"to\": 1272}, {\"ngram\": \"a way\", \"from\": 1281, \"to\": 1286}, {\"ngram\": \"all and bridges political divides\", \"from\": 1304, \"to\": 1337}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Campaigners say they will keep protesting despite a more climate-friendly government having been elected.\", \"from\": 1341, \"to\": 1446, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Campaigners\", \"from\": 1341, \"to\": 1352}, {\"ngram\": \"a more climate-friendly government\", \"from\": 1391, \"to\": 1425}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is because, they say, Labour is maintaining the status quo on many issues, including \\\"using the same outdated climate targets and [they]do not have a planthat is consistent with the Paris agreement, the latest science and global equity\\\".\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1689, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1474, \"end\": 1480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Labour_Party\", \"score\": 0.676678239167693, \"rank\": 0.4772168598660496, \"text\": \"Labour\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Labour_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Labour_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 1634, \"end\": 1649, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_Agreement\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris agreement\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_Agreement\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris_Agreement\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the status quo\", \"from\": 1496, \"to\": 1510}, {\"ngram\": \"many issues\", \"from\": 1514, \"to\": 1525}, {\"ngram\": \"the same outdated climate targets\", \"from\": 1544, \"to\": 1577}, {\"ngram\": \"a planthat\", \"from\": 1600, \"to\": 1610}, {\"ngram\": \"the latest science\", \"from\": 1651, \"to\": 1669}, {\"ngram\": \"global equity\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1687}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Extinction Rebellion predicts that under the threat of legal action from oil companies ministers seem likely to approve licences for North Sea oil drilling issued by the previous government.\", \"from\": 1691, \"to\": 1881, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Extinction Rebellion\", \"from\": 1691, \"to\": 1711}, {\"ngram\": \"the threat\", \"from\": 1732, \"to\": 1742}, {\"ngram\": \"legal action\", \"from\": 1746, \"to\": 1758}, {\"ngram\": \"oil companies ministers\", \"from\": 1764, \"to\": 1787}, {\"ngram\": \"licences\", \"from\": 1811, \"to\": 1819}, {\"ngram\": \"North Sea oil drilling\", \"from\": 1824, \"to\": 1846}, {\"ngram\": \"the previous government\", \"from\": 1857, \"to\": 1880}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It has also pointed out that ministers approved theexpansion of London City airport, and has so far refused to repeal theprevious government's protest laws.\", \"from\": 1882, \"to\": 2038, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1946, \"end\": 1965, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_City_Airport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"London City airport\", \"types\": [\"Q1248784\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_City_Airport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London_City_Airport\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ministers\", \"from\": 1911, \"to\": 1920}, {\"ngram\": \"theexpansion\", \"from\": 1930, \"to\": 1942}, {\"ngram\": \"theprevious government's protest laws\", \"from\": 2000, \"to\": 2037}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Marijn van de Geer, of XR's citizens' assembly working group, said: \\\"Despite vilification from the rightwing media, and new laws putting activists in prison, people are refusing to be silenced and are coming together peacefully to challenge our broken system and to explore together how we can fix it.\", \"from\": 2040, \"to\": 2341, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2054, \"end\": 2058, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Geer_van_Velde\", \"score\": 0.9999667236354682, \"rank\